notes_display: In Historical Sketches of the Paper Currency of the American Colonies by Henry Phillips, Jr. (1865). Given to Dr. Jesse C. Green in 1890. Leaf 56AI.
issue_place_s: Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, United States of America
issue_obverse_legend_s: Fourteen SHILLINGS, according to an Act of General Assembly of Pensylvania, passed in the 13th Year of the Reign of his Majesty GEORGE the Third.  Dated the Twentieth Day of March, Anno Dom. 1773. Fourteen Shillings.
issue_reverse_legend_s: FOURTEEN SHILLINGS. | To Counterfeit, is DEATH.  Printed by  HALL and SELLERS. 1773.
